href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Rio.toList\">toList</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.toList_toArray_rio","kind":"theorem","line":1860,"name":"Nat.toList_toArray_rio","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.lean#L1860-L1863"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.toList_rio_eq_toList_rco\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">toList_rio_eq_toList_rco</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(*...<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Rio.toList\">toList</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">0</span>...<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Rco.toList\">toList</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.toList_rio_eq_toList_rco","kind":"theorem","line":1856,"name":"Nat.toList_rio_eq_toList_rco","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.lean#L1856-L1858"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.induct_roc_right\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">induct_roc_right</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">motive</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">base</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">step</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> (<span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Induction principle for proving properties of `Nat`-based ranges of the form `a<...=b`\nby varying the upper bound.\n\nIn the `base` case, one proves that for any `a : Nat` and `b : Nat` with\n`b ≤ a`, the statement holds for the empty range `a<...=b`.\n\nIn the `step` case, one proves that for any `a : Nat` and `b : Nat`, if the\nstatement holds for `a<...=b`, it also holds for the larger range `a<...=(b + 1)`.\n\nThe following is an example reproving `length_toList_roc`.\n\n```\nexample (a b : Nat) : (a<...=b).toList.length = b - a := by\n  induction a, b using Nat.induct_roc_right\n  case base =>\n    simp only [Nat.toList_roc_eq_nil, List.length_nil, *]; omega\n  case step a b hle ih =>\n    rw [Nat.toList_roc_eq_append (by omega),\n      List.length_append, List.length_singleton, Nat.add_sub_cancel, ih]\n    omega\n```","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.induct_roc_right","kind":"theorem","line":1827,"name":"Nat.induct_roc_right","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.lean#L1827-L1854"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.induct_roc_left\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">induct_roc_left</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">motive</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">base</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">step</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>) <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Induction principle for proving properties of `Nat`-based ranges of the form `a<...=b`\nby varying the lower bound.\n\nIn the `base` case, one proves that for any `a : Nat` and `b : Nat` with\n`b ≤ a`, the statement holds for the empty range `a<...=b`.\n\nIn the `step` case, one proves that for any `a : Nat` and `b : Nat`, the\nstatement holds for nonempty ranges `a<...=b` if it holds for the smaller range\n`(a + 1)<...=b`.\n\nThe following is an example reproving `length_toList_roc`.\n\n```\nexample (a b : Nat) : (a<...=b).toList.length = b - a := by\n  induction a, b using Nat.induct_roc_left\n  case base =>\n    simp only [Nat.toList_roc_eq_nil, List.length_nil, *]; omega\n  case step =>\n    simp only [Nat.toList_roc_eq_cons, List.length_cons, *]; omega\n```","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.induct_roc_left","kind":"theorem","line":1799,"name":"Nat.induct_roc_left","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.lean#L1799-L1825"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">n </span><span class=\"fn\">i </span><span class=\"fn\">fallback</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span>&lt;...=<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Roc.toArray\">toArray</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array.getD\">getD</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback","kind":"theorem","line":1794,"name":"Nat.getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.lean#L1794-L1797"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.getD_toArray_roc_eq_add\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">getD_toArray_roc_eq_add</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">n </span><span class=\"fn\">i </span><span class=\"fn\">fallback</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span>&lt;...=<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Roc.toArray\">toArray</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array.getD\">getD</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.getD_toArray_roc_eq_add","kind":"theorem","line":1789,"name":"Nat.getD_toArray_roc_eq_add","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/68218e876d2a38b1985b8590fff244a83c321783/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.lean#L1789-L1792"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/NatLemmas.html#Nat.getD_toArray_roc\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">getD_toArray_roc</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span cla